<bug>
    <id>466193</id>
    <title>Firefox keeps receiveing mjpeg stream after window/tab has been closed</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; de; rv:1.9.0.4) Gecko/2008102920 Firefox/3.0.4
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; de; rv:1.9.0.4) Gecko/2008102920 Firefox/3.0.4</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">We are using 2 Axis 2100 webcams to show everyone our xmas tree lights.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">The axis cameras send a video stream as mjpeg.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">The Stream displayed correctly, but after closing the window/tab that was being used to view the streams, the stream is kept open.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">When we are closing the Firefox with all windows the stream gets closed.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">one Camera send up to 2 Mbit/s, and with the other its up to 4 mbit/s</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">at one time, we testet it on 10 computers (Win XP / Vista) with upcoming 40 mbit/s bandwith!</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">closing all the tabs but the streams everywhere dont end... our ISP are not happy to us... ok, we closed at all computers the firefox'es an all the streams shutting down</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Many other Users have the same problem, please see the Mozilla Support Forum
http://support.mozilla.com/tiki-view_forum_thread.php?locale=de&amp;forumId=1&amp;comments_parentId=91809</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">1 open the webpage and see the stream</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.3">2 closed the tab</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.4">3 see at the Bandwith Monitor, the Stream is always open!</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.5">(ok you can't see anything because the tab is closed but the bandwith is wasted</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.6">4 to stop the stream close the Firefox with all tabs</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.7">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.8">the Bandwith wasting ends</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">oh my got, when we close the tab at Microsoft IE7 the Stream ends.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
